    "title": "IsInitialBlockDownload() can stop syncing",
    "body": "<!-- Describe the issue -->\r\n<!--- What behavior did you expect? -->\r\n\r\nInitial syncronization should continue till last block will downloaded\r\n\r\n<!--- What was the actual behavior (provide screenshots if the issue is GUI-related)? -->\r\n\r\nInitial synchronization can stopping when there is 24 hours left to a last block\r\n\r\n<!--- How reliably can you reproduce the issue, what are the steps to do so? -->\r\n\r\nI do not know is there are real issue or not. But this line is very strange for me https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/validation.cpp#L1183\r\n\r\nSo synchronization may fail when user is in initial download mode and when to end of synchronization remains 24 hours\r\n\r\nI think it should be like this:\r\n \t    if (chainActive.Tip()->GetBlockTime() < GetTime())\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
